<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 3:25PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Glacier
and northwestern Toole Counties through 400 PM MDT...
At 325 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Cut Bank, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cut Bank and Santa Rita.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
north central Montana.</instruction>
